    <baseline year="2017">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Lack of National Financial Reporting Standards  methodologies for commercial enterprises;
-No National Accountants Certification System;</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2018-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2018-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Guidelines for preparation financial statements according to the National Financial Reporting Standards  for commercial enterprise;
2.Review of the existing accountants training and examination system;
3.Tax verification guidelines to link tax accounting and financial reporting;
4.Recommendations for establishing the National Accountants Certification System;
5.Action Plan and budget for implementation of recommendations.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.Guidelines for preparation financial statements according to the NFRS for commercial enterprises. Introduction of the guidelines will help in a better understanding by private and state commercial enterprises implementation of the new National Financial Reporting Standards and provision of higher quality financial statements in line with international standards to the main users. The document was presented to the stakeholders and discussed in the course of training session. The document is supported by the practical example.
2.In order to achieve the goal the International and National Consultants of the project undertook the review of the existing accountants training and examination system. Based on the outcomes of the conducted review, the International and National Consultants developed a number of Recommendations for establishing the National Accountants Certification System. The International Consultant has also developed the Action Plan and the tentative budget to implement recommendations on establishment of the NACS.  
3.The Tax verification guidelines to link tax accounting and financial reporting have been developed by Mr. Maksat Sahatov, the National Consultant. The guidelines are developed to provide principles and recommendations to the users of unified approach in calculations to improve the data quality. The document has been presented to the stakeholders and discussed in the course of training session.
4.Adoption of the new National Financial Reporting Standards will require establishment of the National Accountants Certification System to ensure adequate skills and qualification of national accountants working in the growing private sector in the country. At present time, the Ministry of Finance and Economy undertakes examination (attestation) of chief accountants working in the public sector, including government ministries, agencies and state-owned enterprises. In a view of the growing private sector in Turkmenistan, there is a need to ensure that a growing number of accountants working in private companies have good qualification and knowledge of the new national financial reporting standards to be able to follow the IFRS principles and to prepare accurate financial reporting.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
   </indicator>
  </result>
